What conclusion can be drawn about the signs of the $\elta \athrm{H}$ and $\elta \athrm{S}$ of a reaction with an equilibrium constant which increases with increasing temperature?

choices.Y: $\elta \athrm{H}$ is positive, no conclusion can be drawn about $\elta \athrm{S}$
choices.Z: $\elta \athrm{H}$ is negative, no conclusion can be drawn about $\elta \athrm{S}$

answer: Y) $\elta \athrm{H}$ is positive, no conclusion can be drawn about $\elta \athrm{S}$

body: Serena, trying to charge her phone, creates a voltaic cell that reduces $\athrm{AuCl_4^-}$ to solid Au and oxidizes solid Cd to $\athrm{Cd^{2 + }}$. When balancing the net ionic equation for the whole cell, what is the ratio of the coefficients of Au and Cd?

A system consists of two metal blocks, one made of copper and one made of iron. The copper block is at 100 Kelvin and the iron one is at 200 Kelvin. The heat capacity of the copper block is 6 Joules per Kelvin and the heat capacity of iron is 2 Joules per Kelvin. The two blocks are allowed to touch and come to equilibrium. In Kelvin, what is the final temperature of the two blocks?

Which of the following statements best describes how an increase in temperature affects the viscosity of gases and liquids?

choices.W: Viscosity increases for a gas and decreases for a liquid
choices.X: Viscosity decreases for a gas and increases for a liquid
choices.Y: Viscosity increases for both gases and liquids
choices.Z: Viscosity decreases for both gases and liquids

answer: W) Viscosity increases for a gas and decreases for a liquid

What apparent wobbling of the moon allows earth observers to view 59% of the moon's surface rather than the expected 50% from its 1-to-1 spin-orbit resonance?

1 meter by 1 meter square plates are made from each of the following materials. Light rays of fixed intensity are shone directly onto each of the following plates. Which of the following materials will cause the plate to experience the largest force from the light?

choices.W: Very dark paint that acts like a black-body
choices.X: Polished metal with perfect specular reflection
choices.Y: Matte finish with perfect diffuse reflection
choices.Z: Uniform glass with an index of refraction equal to that of air

answer: X) Polished metal with perfect specular reflection
